Changes to release 0.1.3
------------------------

- UAM client library initialization memory leak fixed.

Changes to release 0.1.2
------------------------

* Introduced request serial number in UAM messages.
* Introduced an optional method of synchronizing session state
  modification through UAM via spin-locking.
* Introduced a feature of externally programmable session retention
  duration. This works through new UAM RT command.
* Packet filter syntax now accepts alternative rule syntax for
  rate limiting which could be applied to both PASS and DNAT statements.
* Current Filter-Id, traffic, bandwidth and time limits are added 
  to accounting report.
* Ignore malformed UAM messages at UAM server.
* Verify UAM params type at Python driver.
* Automated Python module build added.

Changes to release 0.1.1
------------------------

* WARNING: this sweetspot revision renders your current sweetspot configs
  incompatible! But it is worth updating, read on!
* Network I/O system re-designed to use TUN interface instead of
  attaching directly to network card. This helps to improve performance
  by a factor of 2 or 3 by:
  1) eliminating echo traffic processing
  2) in case of multi-instance setup, this lets separate trafic flows
     by sweetspot instances (policy routing).
  It also improves portability - packet socket interface support is no
  longer required to run sweetspot. System must support TUN/TAP driver,
  though.
* Packet tuples hashing algorithm dramatically improved for better
  hash distribution over data set, what practically eliminated hash
  collisions at lhash storage.
* Dedicated packet validation code dropped (due to parasite traffic
  elimination).
* Hashing algorithm at IP fragments tracking code fixed to distinguish
  packet direction. This helps to reduce hash collision rate.
* Statistics on lhash operation is now collected and logged.
* On-line packet filters reload feature implemented.
* Packet filter syntax now supports port ranges and lists.
* Regular operation logging reduced.

Changes to release 0.0.21
-------------------------

* Re-schedule global SNAT relations expiration for active relations.

Changes to release 0.0.20
-------------------------

* Unbound code in previous release used to cause compilation error.
* Accounting interim interval is now configurable at session-level
  (WARNING: this changed UAM UP command format).
* Repetitive session starts will not reset session duration anymore.
* Handle oversized filter text gracefully. Maximum filter size increased.
* Skip further processing for packets marked as outgoing by the kernel
  what might improve overall performance.
* SNAT endpoints allocation logic completely reworked 

Changes to release 0.0.19
-------------------------

* Fix to SNAT public IP allocation policy that used to pick IPs
  beyond configured SNAT network.
* Fix to an uninitialized out variable in ports-per-IP packing factor
  calculation at SNAT code.

Changes to release 0.0.18
-------------------------

* UAM code now handles larger messages (512 bytes) what was needed
  for storing large chunks of session context.
* Fix to UAM server module to make it ignoring UAM protocol errors.
* File descriptor leak fixed in config file parsing code.
* Memory leaks in SNAT relations, UAM client and on gauge hash entry
  reuse fixed.
* Leaking session context fixed.
* Pretty buffers sizes enlarged.
* Code cleaned up followed -Wall reporting

Changes to release 0.0.17
-------------------------

* Typical setup is now on a single-machine.
* Web auth CGI scripts re-worked to use Perl UAM client.
* SNAT subsystem API reworked for clarity when SNAT is disabled.

Changes to release 0.0.16
-------------------------

* Expire SNAT relations to keep memory footprint within limits.
* Dump TCP and UDP port ranges for SNAT in dedicated RADIUS attributes.
* NAT endpoint management re-designed in a modular way.
* Accounting code re-designed in a modular way on a sub-system grain basis.
* SNAT code now does private->public TCP port mapping more statically
  to facilitate pre-empted SNAT relation recovery.
* Accounting records being generated are now chronologically ordered.
* Event Context implemented (in contrary to session context, this one
  is stateless so it goes directly to accounting).
* RFC2869 Interim accounting generation implemented.
* Count and report Acct-In/Output-Packets.
* Sweet-In/Output-Octets replaced with RFC2869 Acct-In/Output-Gigawords.
* Some VSA attributes renamed to reflect the subsystem they belong to.
* An arbitrary packet filter can now be assigned to captured sessions as well.
* Measure and report bandwidth values (WARNING: UAM protocol changed).
* Multi-instance operation mode implemented.

Changes to release 0.0.15
-------------------------

* IP fragmentation now supported by means of IP fragments tracking.
* Packet checksum regeneration replaced with incremental checksum
  adjustment.

Changes to release 0.0.14
-------------------------

* Intristically foreign to sweetspot parameters of user-name and
  nas-ip-address replaced with a single string-typed "context"
  parameter to be used by outer apps for keeping specific session
  details.
* Fix to ICMP checksum calculation for uneven packet sizes.
* Fix to SNAT endpoint resolution when multiple user-networks is configured.
* Fix to traffic accounting code passing through SNAT.

Changes to release 0.0.13
-------------------------

* Full-cone source NAT is now supported. Besides generic NAT,
  this implementation allows for unambiguous, dynamic pubic<->private
  UDP/TCP/ICMP flow endpoints resolution.
* Major internal re-design. Most importantly, passing packets
  are now represented and handled in form of tuple chains
  (concept borrowed from iptables).
* Debugging facility improved.

Changes to release 0.0.12
-------------------------

* Handle traffic limits/accounting in unsigned long long.
* Session duration & idle times equal to 0 now means no-limit (it 
  also has become the default). Default traffic limit now approaches
  infinity.
* Bugfix to acct-stop-time - acct-start-time == session-duration
  equation.
* Sweetspot is now user interface centric. That is "inward" now universally
  means "coming from user" and vice versa.

Changes to release 0.0.11
-------------------------

* filtering by TCP flags implemented (for directional TCP filtering).
* Bugfix to Acct-Input/Output-Octets swap-over.
* Minor fixes.

Changes to release 0.0.10
-------------------------

* Sessions pool is now indexed by SSLeay's lhash mostly to be able
  to use sparse user network space (e.g. multiple user networks).
* Configuration options user-network & user-netmask replaced with
  a single user-networks setting which accepts a sequence of CIDRs.

Changes to release 0.0.9
------------------------

* UAM protocol redesigned for usability. Session limits
  can now be queried via UAM.
* NAS-IP-Address & User-Name session attributes can now be inherited
  from previous session. The intention is to be able to assign these
  attributes prior to application-specific user authentication (RADIUS
  accounting from AP's, DHCP events) where these attributes may not be 
  available.
* Fixes and cleanups.

